Sage 300 ERP










Sage 300 ERP Customer Ratings and Reviews




 (5 out of 5 stars) 3/12/2015

New user to 300 ERP
We just switched January 1st from Sage 50 to Sage 300 ERP. The transition went smoothly with the size of our company and the number of key strokes. I look forward as we work with our partner, Information Innovators as we expand the usability of the product. We made the transition and were current in 60 days.
—Don G.











 (5 out of 5 stars) 3/12/2015

99% awesome - 1% to improve
We converted to Sage last January 2014 from an IBM based product!  Although any software conversion is work, this one went as smoothly as humanly possible and our business partners - Keystone Business Solutions were awesome! We love the flexibility to view things before printing, paperless office to save trees, ease of working between various modules due to the similarities between modules.
One small thing in payroll that has to be an oversight is related to benefit deductions. There is no way to put a beginning or ending date in a benefit. This makes it difficult at open enrollment for insurance as we are a weekly pay company, so I have one week to remove or add or make any changes to benefits for 350 people.
—CPAsinger











 (5 out of 5 stars) 3/10/2015
Great Experience

Sage has helped our team be more productive and give my company the reports, tools to gain more business.
—Elizabeth











 (5 out of 5 stars) 3/10/2015
Sage is great!
Sage is user friendly and has so many options to promote employee performance and functionality.
—e louise











 (5 out of 5 stars) 3/10/2015
review sage 300
We really like sage 300. It really helps during our analysis to be able to change what is visible on the G/L.
—Hadley











 (3 out of 5 stars) 3/10/2015
Sage 300

This is my first experience with Sage. I was on SAP before. I have found that it is very user friendly. It was easy to learn to use.
—Diana











 (4 out of 5 stars) 3/10/2015
Sage is working great for our needs, I just need to learn how to use more of it!
We really need to focus on learning how to use Sage to better fit our needs. I know we haven't even scraped the surface of what it can do for us. The support at Sage has been really helpful and I can't wait to learn more.
—Dana W.











 (4 out of 5 stars) 3/10/2015
Senior accountant
Sage 300 is good for documents controlling, vendors information and G/L reports. Need more implementation on job costing and reports by jobs.
—Ana L.











 (5 out of 5 stars) 2/6/2015
love it and my orchid
Thanks to Sage 300 ERP and our orchid software my team is more efficient and effective in our weekly processes and our periodic reporting. We have a fabulous macro that brings our weekly production and payment data seamlessly from our IBM Cognos system painlessly to Sage. We love the ao offset functionality. It again allows us to quickly and efficiently do our a/r and a/p offset process.  And finally the orchid add-on makes our EFT payment processing process absolutely painless.
Anne-Marie B.











 (4 out of 5 stars) 2/5/2015
Segment codes are invaluable
As a charity operating essentially 300 distinct departments, Sage 300 gives us the flexibility to provide the data our employees need.
Ken











 (4 out of 5 stars) 2/5/2015
I am learning it very easily
Sage is great for beginners. It has been around so long so it is very trustworthy. It is always keeping up with its competition.
Arielle B.











 (4 out of 5 stars) 2/5/2015
Works Great for most of our business needs
We are a distributor with light manufacturing and retail.  Sage 300 fits most of our needs out of the box.
Mike























